  "text": "The other branch of this work characterises the lexical cohesion using topic models, to which the model introduced in Section 3 belongs. Lexical cohesion in this line of research is modelled by a probabilistic generative process. PLDA presented by [CITATION_1] is an unsupervised topic modelling approach for segmentation. It chains a set of LDAs [CITATION_2] by assuming a Markov structure on topic distributions. A binary topic shift variable is attached to each text passage (i.e., an utterance in [CITATION_3] ). It is sampled to indicate whether the j th text passage shares the topic distribution with the (j − 1) th passage.",
